\shape default
\size default
\emph default
\bar default
\noun default
\color inherit
 is (conditional) maximum likelihood estimate from 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

 data points when 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{r}\geq1$
\end_inset

, so it can be effectively encoded with 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{1}{2}log_{2}n$
\end_inset

 bits.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula $L(\hat{b_{0}})=\cdots=L(\hat{b_{\hat{r}}})=L(\hat{\beta_{1}})=\cdots=L(\hat{\beta_{\hat{m}}})=\frac{1}{2}log_{2}n$
\end_inset

, so
